sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT product_id) AS count_of_unsold_products
FROM products
WHERE product_id NOT IN (SELECT product_id FROM sales);

external_knowledge:
- "shines the brightest" refers to the category with the highest average sale price;
- "top 3 products" means the products with the highest total revenue in that category;
- "total revenue" is the sum of all sales for a product;
- "average price of the category" is the average sale price of all products in the top category.

sql:
SELECT MAX(total_revenue) AS highest_total_revenue
FROM (
    SELECT s.product_id, SUM(s.total_price) AS total_revenue
    FROM sales s
    GROUP BY s.product_id
) AS product_revenue;

